To build the Matter over Wi-Fi sample variant on nRF5340 DK with nRF7002 EK shield attached, perform the following actions depending on the build tool:

.. tabs::

   .. group-tab:: nRF Connect for VS Code

      1. When `building an application <How to build an application_>`_ as described in the |nRFVSC| documentation, follow the steps for setting up the build configuration.
      #. In the **Add Build Configuration** screen, click the **Add argument** button under the **Extra CMake argument** section.
      #. Add the following Kconfig options:

         .. code-block:: console

            -- -DSHIELD=nrf7002ek -DFILE_SUFFIX=nrf70ek -DSB_CONFIG_WIFI_NRF70=y

   .. group-tab:: Command line

      You can use one of the following options:

      * west with the following command:

        .. code-block:: console

           west build -p -b nrf5340dk/nrf5340/cpuapp -- -DSHIELD=nrf7002ek -DFILE_SUFFIX=nrf70ek -DSB_CONFIG_WIFI_NRF70=y

      * CMake with the following command:

        .. code-block:: console

           cmake -GNinja -Bbuild -DBOARD=nrf5340dk/nrf5340/cpuapp -DSHIELD=nrf7002ek -DFILE_SUFFIX=nrf70ek -DSB_CONFIG_WIFI_NRF70=y -DAPP_DIR=*app_path* *path_to_zephyr*/share/sysbuild
           ninja -C build
